-- Credit Suisse, Logitech, Swatch, UBS May Be Active: Swiss Stock Preview
-- Alexis Xydias
-- 2010-07-08T06:32:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-08/credit-suisse-logitech-swatch-ubs-may-be-active-swiss-stock-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies’ shares may
be active in Zurich. Stock symbols are in parentheses after
company names. Prices are from the last close.  
 The  Swiss Market Index  of the biggest and most actively
traded companies advanced 36.08, or 0.6 percent, to 6,099.2. The
broader  Swiss Performance Index  rose 0.6 percent to 5,388.17.  
 Credit Suisse Group AG  (CSGN VX) and  UBS AG  (UBSN VX): The
Swiss Financial Market Supervisory Authority, or Finma, is
examining whether it will publish stress-test results of the two
banks, Swiss daily Tagesanzeiger reported, citing Finma
spokesman Tobias Lux. Credit Suisse rose 2.7 percent to 42.9
Swiss francs. UBS gained 1.9 percent to 14.83 francs.  
 Logitech International S.A.  (LOGN VX): The maker of
computer hardware agreed to buy assets from Norway’s Paradial
AS, a provider of firewall solutions for video communications,
according to a regulatory filing. Financial terms were not
disclosed. The shares rose 0.4 percent to 14.55 francs.  
      Swatch Group AG  (UHR VX): The watchmaker is maintaining its
policy of not selling watch components to rivals, and talks with
Switzerland’s competition regulator on how to do so are
continuing, Le Temps reported, citing an interview with Chief
Executive Officer Nick Hayek Jr. The shares fell 0.3 percent to
304.6 francs.  
